Successful Request <p>Response 200 OK</p> <pre><code>{
    "envelope": {
        "invoices": [
            {
                "invoiceReferenceNumber": "XYZ26001280",
                "dateIssued": "20260109",
                "modelType": "Invoice",
                "invoiceAttachment": "https://cdn.swift-navigator.com/api/documents/d/yGnBTCqNteN"
            },
            {
                "invoiceReferenceNumber": "XYZ26001281",
                "dateIssued": "20260112",
                "modelType": "Invoice",
                "invoiceAttachment": "https://cdn.swift-navigator.com/api/documents/d/6JgN99GAoXd"
            },
            {
                "invoiceReferenceNumber": "XYZ26001282",
                "dateIssued": "20260113",
                "modelType": "Credit Note",
                "invoiceAttachment": "https://cdn.swift-navigator.com/api/documents/d/8RFgsYFjuvq"
            }
        ]
    }
}
</code></pre> Information <ul> <li>invoiceReferenceNumber is the reference number of each invoice issued. Reference number is used as key in the Retrieve Invoice API, to retreive the JSON &amp; PDF formats of the invoice (or credit note).</li> <li>invoiceAttachment contains the public address of the invoice in PDF format and will remain available for download for up to two (2) months after issuance. The URL exists also in the Retrieve Invoice API.</li> </ul> Client Error <p>Response 401 Unauthorized Response 405 Method Not Allowed Response 429 Too Many Requests</p> <pre><code>{
    "error": " ... "
}
</code></pre> Server Error <p>Response 500 Internal Server Error Response 502 Bad Gateway Response 503 Service Unavailable</p> <pre><code>{
    "error": " ... "
}
</code></pre>
